<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1058,401,569]" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" box="[462,559,401,422]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="970" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[462,559,401,422]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">Perilypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
SPINOLA was revised in 1977 (EKIS 1977). This work included a key to species. The available 
<taxonomicName box="[634,832,430,452]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="968" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apunctus">
<emphasis box="[634,832,430,452]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">Perilypus apunctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen keys out to 
<emphasis box="[151,279,459,481]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">P. distinctus</emphasis>
EKIS, from which the 
<taxonomicName box="[523,645,460,481]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="968" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apunctus">
<emphasis box="[523,645,460,481]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">P. apunctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen differs by showing a phallobasic lobe that is not uncinate. The aedeagus of the 
<taxonomicName box="[684,804,489,510]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="968" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apunctus">
<emphasis box="[684,804,489,510]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">P. apunctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen is also similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[268,400,518,540]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="968" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virgulatus">
<emphasis box="[268,400,518,540]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">P. virgulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the phallobasic lobes are significantly more elongate in the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,270,548,569]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="968" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apunctus">
<emphasis box="[151,270,548,569]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">P. apunctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1059,584,929]" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 9.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[673,753,584,606]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="968" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,585,607]" captionStart="Figs 270-273" captionStartId="95.[151,191,1512,1534]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,224,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@95.[153,1061,196,1495]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="Figs 270-273: Habitus; (270) Aphelocerus yoro; (271) Perilypus alpinus; (272) P. apunctus; (273) P. arsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746796" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746796/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">Fig. 272</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium, prothorax, and mesosternum yellow; antenna black, except scape yellow; metathorax black; elytra dull violaceous; legs bicolorous, femora yellow, infuscated apically, tibiae and tarsi black. Head: Interocular depression shallow, crescentic; frontal umbo not prominent; cranium minutely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation box="[765,840,702,724]" captionStart="Figs 1-27" captionStartId="70.[151,191,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[155,1057,207,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[155,1058,207,1283]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figs 1-27: Antennae; (1) Aphelocerus nodus; (2) A. copanus; (3) A. magnipannus; (4) A. yoro; (5) A. sparicapillus; (6) A. tigra. (7) A. nolus; (8) A. ligulus; (9) Perilypus schusteri; (10) P. apunctus; (11) P. virgulatus; (12) P. izabal; (13) P. alpinus; (14) Cregya fuscomacula; (15) Phonius versus; (16) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (17) Pelonium falcatum; (18) Pujoliclerus cnecostus; (19) P. trunculus. (20) P. sentus; (21) P. testudinatus; (22) P. catie; (23) P. flavidus; (24) P. convexus; (25) P. meloinus; (26) P. mexicoensis; (27) P. tuxtlas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746746/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) serrate, not densely setose, antennomeres gradually increasing in diameter from scape to antennomere 11; eyes finely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 30/40). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 92-100" captionStartId="74.[151,191,872,894]" captionTargetBox="[175,1038,229,838]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[155,1062,203,862]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="Figs 92-100: Antennae; (92) Pyticeroides desodes; (93) Ichnea cerinis; (94) Agnatis vaurieae; (95) Ampleris amazon; (96) Nepsudia guenda; (97) Isoparis cassidilis; (98) Pelonium atrigonatium; (99) Aphelocerus yaguare; (100) Madoniella selvanegra." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746754/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
) transverse, very finely punctate; pronotal arch well defined; subapical depression well defined; side margins of pronotum proper strongly arcuate (PW/PL 105/90); elytra oblong rectangulate, pubescence short and profusely distributed throughout disc; disc punctures small and profusely distributed on disc, epipleural fold plane (EL/EW 340/85). Abdomen: Pygidium transverse 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[472,479,907,929]" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">/</emphasis>
scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[742,834,907,929]" captionStart="Figs 207-212" captionStartId="84.[151,191,1256,1278]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,199,1242]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[153,1061,199,1242]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="Figs 207-212: Aedeagi; (207) Aphelocerus tigra; (208) A. yoro; (209) Perilypus alpinus; (210) P. apunctus; (211) P. arsus; (212) P. izabal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746774/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="968">Fig. 210.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
